(373, 'Sri Lanka seal ODI series against South Africa', 'COLOMBO: Debutant spinner Maheesh Theekshana claimed four wickets as Sri Lanka hammered South Africa by 78 runs in the third One-day International to clinch the series 2-1 in Colombo on Tuesday.', '<p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Theekshana, an off-spinner with a lethal carrom ball, returned figures of 4-37 as the hosts bowled out South Africa for 125 in 30 overs while chasing a target of 204 at the R. Premadasa Stadium.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">The 21-year-old Theekshana made an instant impact with a wicket of his first delivery in international cricket as he sent opener Janneman Malan trudging back for 18.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Rain then stopped play briefly.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">He then cut short wicket-keeper/batter Heinrich Klaasen’s innings on 22 to further dent the Proteas chase.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Andile Phehlukwayo, who made 17, and George Linde, who scored 18, put up some resistance with a partnership of 36 for the seventh wicket.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Theekshana combined with leg-spinner Wanindu Hasaranga, who took two wickets to polish off the tail with 20 overs remaining in the innings.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Pace bowler Dushmantha Chameera took two early wickets including Reeza Hendricks, for one, and Rassie van der Dussen, for five, to rattle the South African top-order.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Earlier stand-in skipper Keshav Maharaj took three wickets as Sri Lanka made 203 for nine.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Charith Asalanka was the top-scorer with 47 and player-of-the-match Chameera, coming in at number nine, hit a useful 29.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Maharaj struck first, getting the in-form Avishka Fernando lbw for 10, and returned figures of 3-38 with his left-arm spin. Fellow spinners George Linde and Tabraiz Shamsi claimed two wickets each.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">South Africa successfully reviewed the openers’ wickets in their favour after Fernando and Dinesh Chandimal, out lbw for nine off left-arm orthodox Linde, were given not out by the on-field umpires.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Spinners kept striking as Aiden Markram sent back Dhananjaya de Silva for 31 and Maharaj got two including skipper Dasun Shanaka and Hasaranga as Sri Lanka slipped to 121-6.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Asalanka, who was later declared player-of-the-series, survived a reprieve on 36 when he was caught at mid-wicket off Linde but the delivery was adjudged a no ball with more fielders outside the inner circle than allowed.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">Shamsi, a left-arm wrist spinner, finally got Asalanka caught behind to deny the left-hand batsman a half-century.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">The two sides will now play three Twenty20 Internationals starting from Friday at the same venue.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); font-weight: bolder;\">Scoreboard</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); font-weight: bolder;\">SRI LANKA:</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">W.I.A. Fernando lbw b Maharaj 10</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">L.D. Chandimal lbw b Linde 9</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">P.H.K.D. Mendis c and b George Linde 16</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">D.M. de Silva c Klaasen b Markram 31</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">K.I.C. Asalanka c Klaasen b Shamsi 47</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">M.D. Shanaka c Mulder b Maharaj 13</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">W. Hasaranga c Hendricks b Maharaj 6</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">C. Karunaratne lbw b Shamsi 16</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">P.V.D. Chameera c Malan b Mulder 29</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">M.M. Theekshana not out 10</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">P. Jayawickrama not out 2</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">EXTRAS (LB-2, W-8, NB-4) 14</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">TOTAL (for nine wkts, 50 overs) 203</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">FALL OF WKTS: 1-22, 2-33, 3-64, 4-93, 5-112, 6-121, 7-154, 8-166, 9-198.</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">BOWLING: Rabada 8-0-46-0 (3nb, 6w); Maharaja 10-0-38-3; Linde 10-1-32-2 (1nb); Markram 10-1-41-1; Shamsi 10-0-31-2 (1w); Phehlukwayo 1-0-10-0; Mulder 1-0-3-1 (1w).</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); font-weight: bolder;\">SOUTH AFRICA:</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">J.N. Malan c de Silva b Theekshana 10</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">A. Markram c de Silva b Jayawickrama 2</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">R. Hendricks b Chameera 1</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">H.E. van der Dussen c Mendis b Chameera 5</p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(210, 214, 220); margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-left: auto; line-height: 1.7; font-family: Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px;\">H. Klaasen lbw